    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-meat-free-bacon-lentil-and-smashed-avocado-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>meat-free bacon lardons</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden and crisp</p><p>Once the meat-free bacon is crisp, add it to a plate lined with kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and set aside, reserving the pan</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-meat-free-bacon-lentil-and-smashed-avocado-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-meat-free-bacon-lentil-and-smashed-avocado-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with any remaining oil and add the <strong>drained lentils </strong>along with <strong>half </strong>of your<strong> chilli relish </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Mix it all together and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through \u2013 these are your<strong> seasoned lentils</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-meat-free-bacon-lentil-and-smashed-avocado-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the lentils are cooking, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong> to a small bowl with your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli relish dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-meat-free-bacon-lentil-and-smashed-avocado-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>crispy meat-free bacon</strong> <strong>lardons </strong>to a clean board and chop roughly</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-meat-free-bacon-lentil-and-smashed-avocado-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>seasoned lentils</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>salad</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>crispy meat-free bacon</strong> <strong>lardons </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy meat-free bacon & lentil salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-meat-free-bacon-lentil-and-smashed-avocado-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy meat-free bacon & lentil salad</strong> with your <strong>smashed avocado </strong>over the top</p><p>Crumble over your <strong>feta </strong>and drizzle with the <strong>chilli relish dressing</strong></p><p>Top with your <strong>pumpkin seeds </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>crispy meat-free bacon lardons</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
